iteminfo.name: Lunar Rabbit Fortune's Gate
iteminfo.nameWorkshop: Lunar Rabbit Fortune's Gate | Garage Door [Glow]
iteminfo.descriptionWorkshop:
/wskin wall.frame.garagedoor 2915557035

To celebrate the Chinese New Lunar Year, the Year of the Water Rabbit, we have created a skin that is inspired by cultural Chinese elements. Every aspect of this skin has been designed and crafted from scratch.


[img]https://i.imgur.com/hID6zwB.gif[/img]

Story:
It was a cold and dreary winter day when the old lady sat in her small and cramped workshop. She was sick and weak, but she refused to let that stop her from completing the project that she had been working on for months.
Despite the pain in her joints and the difficulty in breathing, the old lady persevered, determined to finish the beautiful handmade garage door that she had named "Fortune's Gate."

She had created the door for her beloved grandchild, a young girl who brought joy and light into her life even on the darkest of days. The old lady wanted to give her grandchild something special to start the new year, a symbol of luck, prosperity, wealth, and longevity.

As she worked, the old lady took great care to include intricate details and symbols on the door. In the center, she carved a beautiful rabbit, a symbol of good fortune in Chinese culture. And around the edges of the door, she etched the characters for luck, prosperity, wealth, and longevity.

But perhaps the most special touch was the hidden message that the old lady left for her grandchild. In the darkness of the workshop, the old lady carefully wrote the words "Happy New Year" in Chinese on the inside of the door's curtains. She hoped that when her grandchild opened the door on New Year's Day, the message would bring her comfort and warmth.

Unfortunately, the old lady never got to see her grandchild open the door. She passed away before the new year, leaving behind the beautiful gift that she had worked so hard to create.
But even in death, the old lady's love and care for her grandchild lived on through the "Fortune's Gate" that she had so carefully crafted. And as the young girl opened the door on that cold and dreary winter day, she felt a warmth and love that she knew came from her dear grandmother.
